article.headline: High Point 76, Radford 62
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- High Point's Troy Bowen scored 18 points to lead the Panthers to a 76-62 victory over Radford in a Big South Conference game Wednesday night. Bowen, who connected on four-of-six 3-pointers, was one of five players to score in double figures for High Point (12-7, 5-4 Big South). Also scoring in double figures were Issa Konare, 13 points; Akeem Scott, 11 points; and Mike Jefferson and Melvin Crowder, 10 points each. Arizona Reid had 13 rebounds for the Panthers. Reggie McIntyre led Radford (12-9, 5-4) with 14 points. Chris Oliver scored 13 points and Whit Holcomb-Faye added 10. High Point led 32-19 at the 8:18 mark of the first half, but an 11-0 scoring run by Radford cut the Panthers' lead to two points. Holcomb-Faye connected on a long 3-pointer at the halftime buzzer, giving the Highlanders a 39-37 lead at the break. High Point went ahead 54-45 with 14:13 left in the game with a 13-2 scoring run. Radford never got closer than seven points over the final 10 minutes of the game.
